<doc id="716736" wikidata="Q7269416" url="?curid=716736" title="Quasar, Quasar, Burning Bright">
<text>Quasar, Quasar, Burning Bright is a collection of seventeen scientific essays by American writer and scientist Isaac Asimov. It was the thirteenth of a series of books collecting essays from &quot;The Magazine of Fantasy and Science Fiction&quot;. These essays were first published between May 1976 and September 1977. It was first published by Doubleday &amp; Company in 1978. Its title is derived from the first line of William Blake&#x27;s 1794 poem &quot;The Tyger&quot;.

