<doc id="716766" wikidata="Q1936542" url="?curid=716766" title="Gold (Asimov book)">
<text>Gold: The Final Science Fiction Collection is a 1995 collection of stories and essays by American writer Isaac Asimov. The stories, which comprise the volume&#x27;s first half, are short pieces which had remained uncollected at the time of the author&#x27;s death. &quot;Cal&quot; describes a robot that wishes to write, and the title story &quot;Gold&quot; expresses both Asimov&#x27;s admiration of &quot;King Lear&quot; and his thoughts on cinema adaptations of his own stories. The story &quot;Gold&quot; won a Hugo Award.

